definitions.definition: To obtain a successful outcome by pure chance.
examples: I fluked a pass in the multiple-choice exam.

definitions.definition: To fortuitously pot a ball in an unintended way.
examples: He fluked the other red into the middle pocket, despite the double kiss.

main_definition: To obtain a successful outcome by pure chance.
secondary_definitions: ( snooker ) To fortuitously pot a ball in an unintended way.
